caption:
Table 1: Comparison with the state-of-the-art methods on R2R. Blue indicates the best value in a given setting. S indicates 
the single-instruction setting, M indicates the multiple-instruction setting.
Table 2: Results on CVDN measured by Goal Progress. Blue indicates the best value in a given setting.

Table 3: Results on test splits of HANNA. The agent with "perfect assistance" uses the teacher navigation policy to make 
decisions when executing a subtask from the assistant. Blue indicates the best value.
Table 4: Ablation study of the pre-training objectives on CVDN, measured by Goal Progress. Blue indicates the best value.
Table 5: Ablation study on R2R: feature-based vs fine-tuning. Blue indicates the better value.
Table 7: Ablation study of pre-training objectives on test splits of HANNA.
